de.hsbremen.tc.tnc.exception.enums

Enum TncExceptionCodeEnum

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TncExceptionCodeEnum>
      • de.hsbremen.tc.tnc.exception.enums.TncExceptionCodeEnum
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<TncExceptionCodeEnum>

    public enum TncExceptionCodeEnum
extends Enum<TncExceptionCodeEnum>
    Enumeration of known result codes for exceptions at the IF-IMC/V interface.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      TNC_RESULT_ALREADY_INITIALIZED
      The IMC or IMV's initialize method was called twice without a call to the IMC or IMV's terminate method.
      TNC_RESULT_CANT_RESPOND
      IMC or IMV cannot respond now.
      TNC_RESULT_CANT_RETRY
      TNCC or TNCS cannot attempt handshake retry.
      TNC_RESULT_EXCEEDED_MAX_MESSAGE_SIZE
      Exceeded maximum message size supported by the underlying protocol.
      TNC_RESULT_EXCEEDED_MAX_ROUND_TRIPS
      Exceeded maximum round trips supported by the underlying protocol.
      TNC_RESULT_FATAL
      Unspecified fatal error.
      TNC_RESULT_ILLEGAL_OPERATION
      Illegal operation attempted.
      TNC_RESULT_INVALID_PARAMETER
      Method parameter is not valid.
      TNC_RESULT_NO_LONG_MESSAGE_TYPES
      Connection does not support long message types.
      TNC_RESULT_NO_SOH_SUPPORT
      Connection does not support SOH.
      TNC_RESULT_NOT_INITIALIZED
      The IMC or IMV's initialize method has not been called.
      TNC_RESULT_OTHER
      Unspecified error.
      TNC_RESULT_WONT_RETRY
      TNCC or TNCS refuses to attempt handshake retry.
